==English==
{{wikipedia}}
===Etymology===
From surname of [[w:Joseph Louis François Bertrand|Joseph Louis François Bertrand]], who conjectured the theorem and surname of [[w:Pafnuty Chebyshev|Pafnuty Chebyshev]] who proved it.

===Noun===
'''Bertrand-Chebyshev theorem'''

# {{cattag|mathematics}} the theorem that there is at least one [[prime]] number between ''n'' and 2''n'' for every ''n''>1, i.e.:
#: <math>\forall n\in\mathbb{N}:n>1\Rightarrow\exists p\in\mathbb{P}:n<p<2n</math>